    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.65"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">65</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Drawing of mountains within two squares</figDesc>
                        <p>OFFICE OF RESIDENT THEOLOGIAN CU</p>  
                    </figure>
                
                    <hi rend="caps">ST. THOMAS AQUINAS NEWMAN CENTER</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    904 14th Street
                        <lb/>
                    Boulder, Colorado 80302     Phones: 443-8383
                        <lb/>
                                                        443-8384
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>October 20, 1972</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>c/o University of Nebraska Press</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>University of Nebraska</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Heavy scheduling of facilities at the University has forced us to reserve a specific date for the <hi rend="underline">Spirit and Society</hi> conference we wrote to you about on October 5. It will be held Tuesday through Friday, February 27, 28, March 1 and 2.</p>
                
                <p>We are sorry that because of failing health you will be unable to join us for the conference but if you should feel well enough in the spring and could participate please let us know.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Robert Ludwig</signed>
                    <signed>Robert Ludwig, Theologian-in-Residence</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
